subSubSection.paragraph:
Prothorax black with following areas blue: anterior lobe, dorsolateral spot on middle lobe, narrow elongate diagonal spot on lateral portion of propleuron with posterior margin rimmed in black. Pale areas of pterothorax vivid blue, with black middorsal stripe slightly narrowed at basal 0.20, about as wide as blue antehumeral stripe; anterior half of mesinfraepisternum black, continuous with broad humeral stripe at base then abruptly narrowing at basal fifth along mesopleural suture then abruptly forming a thin hairline at 0.50 before expanding again at mesopleural fossa; remainder of thorax blue except for narrow black stripe on metapleural suture (
Fig. 17
). Wings hyaline with venation black; pterostigma dark brown, surmounting 1 cell in all wings; postnodals Fw 15/16, Hw 15/14; postquadrangular cells Fw 4/4, Hw 3/3; RP2 at Fw 7/7, Hw 5/5.5. Coxae and trochanters pale except for black on dorsum of trochanters; femora black, interior surface pale; tibiae black with extensor surface pale, tarsi and armature black.
